parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause the vehicle's suspension to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on tires.
symptoms: The ball joints are worn or corroded
the ball joints separate
the "A" frame drops down onto the road
the vehicle's suspension collapses
the tires wear prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission's failure to shift into forward gears can cause the vehicle to become stuck or immobile, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission does not shift into any forward gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seal can cause brake fluid to leak onto the brake shoes, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks onto the brake shoes
the vehicle's braking performance is reduced
the vehicle's stopping distance is increased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CV boot can cause the CV joint to wear prematurely, leading to vibrations, noise, and loss of vehicle control, which can cause accidents.

the CV boot is damaged or torn.
